Informed consent to participate in research

In this study, we are interested in how people make decisions. If you agree to be in this study, you will play a decision-making game, as well as answer some brief demographic questions and some questionnaires. The estimated time to complete this study is approximately 20 minutes.  The research is being conducted with the goal of publication in academic journals and presentation at academic conferences.



Risks

Your participation in this study does not involve any physical risk or emotional risk to you beyond the risks of daily life.



Compensation

You will receive the amount specified in the description of the study for your participation. In addition, you may earn a bonus based on your decision in the game, as detailed in the instructions of the study.

The bonus will be paid after some delay - once we have collected the responses of all the participants in the study. 



Confidentiality

The data you provide will be collected through a secure online system called Amazon Mechanical Turk. The collected data will be fully anonymized and confidentiality will be maintained. We may report the data in scientific publications and the data may ultimately be stored in online repositories so that other researchers can utilize this information in future research. However, any such data will be completely anonymized and you will not in any way be identifiable from the data stored online or reported in publications.



Contacts

If there is anything about the study or taking part in it that is unclear or that you do not understand, please contact the researcher of this study, through a message in the messaging system.



Subject rights

Participation in this study is voluntary, and you are free to leave the study at any time. If you withdraw at any time, you will receive no monetary compensation.

Interesting study overall I am excited to hear the goal :)

Q89:
Hello, I hope you are doing well. I am a born again Christian, so I do not believe in luck as a Christian.  Colossians 2:8 and 15, I believe there are things as luck and such for people who have not given their life to God, for people who do not believe in God. Such people and Christians who do not believe in Jesus to give up control, do gamble and say things like "He is so lucky, they got that money from that thing" or "He messed up but he managed to get away without trouble, so lucky" etc. The life people live in this world is uncertainty and this brings fear and then greed and other sins. Through Jesus I have certainty, that job I lost, God will provide another. Through Jesus I am no longer a servant of God but a son. Along with that comes the security of a son; the love, grace, mercy, forgiveness and blessings of a father is not shown depending on our goodness, actions or abilities but rather because we are children. Luke 15:11-32 we see the story of the prodigal son, he takes his inheritance and lives a life of sin and mess. He remembers the love of his father, the goodness to his servants and decides to go back. In verse 20 we see the love of the father, a love that keeps no record of wrong doing. A fatherly love that is unconditional. People struggle to see God as a father because of bad relationships with earthly fathers, me included.

In Psalms 23:1 David talks about God, he talks about His reliance on God, which is reflected in him bringing down Goliath. He brings glory to God and declares victory before evening fighting. 1 Samuel 17:45-47 David proclaims God doing the work for Him. So is the same in my life though Christ. In the Old Testament, it was for the Israelites but through Christian, a wild olive branch like me is grafted into the original. 

Furthermore the love of God for mankind is seen in Genesis 3:9 after Adam and Eve disobeyed God. I refuse to believe a God who knitted me in my mother's womb did not know they had sinned. Yet as a father He called to His children in verse, instead of casting them out straight away. He gave them a chance to own up to their sins in verse 11, yet they pass the blame. If only they had admitted their sin, how different of a world would we be living in. 

Yet through Christ, I gain all that Adam lost Romans 5:12 and 15, I get the relationship of a father and son, I get the security Adam and Eve had, they did not work on the land for food, they had priesthood, ability to worship God, prophethood, being able to hear the word of God and kingship, they were the rulers of earth, they had authority and prosperity. This was handed to Satan because these positions were empty. Through Christ I receive it all. He came as man to overcome the devil that I may reign with Him. 

This is why I do not believe in luck. My God has willed and has given me more than luck could ever. Through "luck" you might get the right job, meet the right wife, have healthy children, earn money for a good house etc. Through Jesus I know I will receive this and more it is a matter of timing. Currently I am waiting to start my MSc. I was so opposed it because I struggled so much with my BSc. I did not want to go through it again. Even then God helped me. I had preachers prophecy it was the will of God for me to do a masters and even a PhD. I do not see what will happen exactly i.e. i will get a job in this company etc. But there are prophecies that this is for a better job. There is prophecy that I don't have to worry about my future wife. I could not believe it, what God said was "Don't worry". A lady at Church came and said this to me when I was falling for a girl at Church. I struggled with self love for so long because I am fat and my family is adament in letting me know it. They tell me about the year i wasted during my gap year, and somany other failings and inequalities. But God who chose David, who is believed to be a child born between Jesse and his sister, if God cares about someone's character rather than anything else, how much security can I have in God to help me? I can believe in God to provide me a wife to love and cherish me even with my stretch marks and other imperfections. This is the certainty I have. Not in luck, my abilities or goodness, but the goodness and unconditional love of my father, who suffered at the hands of His creation to free me from the ways of this world, to give me this security. I hope your eyes are opened and blessed with this security too. 

You may have a question about suffering, but suffering is caused by human greed isn't it? The UN sent food aid to North Korea and they instead sell it to their people while orphans pick up pieces of corn from the mud that is dropped as crumbs. I have seen the video. Same with health care and all the such, the greed of humans is what causes suffering. Through Christ I am free from that too. 

All the best with your work, God bless.
